Entry.19: Left Paddington 6.45 arrived Devonport went aboard tender got on Fredrichsruh about four had supper left five minutes to one in morning seasick all day
Entry.21: On guard four hours smooth sea feeling well Band afternoon
Entry.22: Beautiful day passed Gibraltar and Morrocco about eleven very calm in Mediteranean
Entry.23: Still glorious weather passing along coast all day passed Algiers in afternoon dancing on deck at night
Entry.24: Still smooth sea glorious weather on guard four hours morning same afternoon
Entry.25: again Sunday Arrived Port said nine o’clock entered Canal tied up ten o’clock to coal loading finished sailed about midnight. no leave granted left about midnight
Entry.26: In canal several steamers passed, passed Karitara arrived Suez about nine o’clock anchored for about three hours on
Entry.29: Still in Red Sea very hot passed several ships during day
Entry.30: Last day in Red Sea. passed several steamers also troopships going towards Suez also saw passenger ship on rocks , passed several islands Apostles Hells Gate Perim at night
Entry.31: Got of Red Sea on deck picket sports afternoon
Entry.32: Church Parade in morning still very hot
Entry.33: Concert at night passed several ships during day
Entry.34: Voyage getting dreary band concert at night medical inspection in day
Entry.37: On guard looking forward to Colombo
Entry.38: Arrived Colombo midday sweltering heat. Went ashore half past two went to Cinnamon Gardens, Buddist Temple, Fruit Markets around city in rickshaw, nightime went out to Grand Pass returned to ship about ten o’clock
Entry.39: Finished coaling and taking water left Colombo three o’clock very hot.
Entry.40: old sea day very hot travelling last lap to Australia very slow
Entry.42:

Boxing afternoon Concert at night
Entry.44: old thing Boxing afternoon sea getting rough
Entry.46: On guard sea calmer boxing afternoon
Entry.47: Boxing again band concert again at night
Entry.48: Sea getting rough concert at night getting fixed up with demob papers
Entry.49: Broke down in ocean drifting about nine hours Osterley passed midday
Entry.51: Arrived Fremantle midday on guard went ashore and up to Perth at nightime very tame.
Entry.52: Went up to Perth afternoon went to Nedlands Park, Kings Park night time to Government Gardens
Entry.53: Went to Perth again boat not ready came aboard ready to sail ships crew struck work
Entry.54: Still at Fremantle things not too good. Pushed out 2-30 several missed boat squabbles everywhere
Entry.55: At sea boat going good after being repaired
Entry.56: On guard guard a bit stricter than usual lovely day in the bight very smooth
Entry.58: Getting a bit rough ship rolled very heavy during night
Entry.60: A bit better farewell concert by band
Entry.61: Arrived Melbourne nine o’clock afternoon and night ashore good time Victorians, S. Aus, Tasmanians left ship
Entry.62: Left Melbourne seven o’clock in morning sea very smooth ship very deserted looking
Entry.63:
Still at sea very calm ship going very slow got paid disembarkation pay
